      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> to a bowl with 1/4<strong> </strong>of the <strong>diced shallot<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and set aside — this is your <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>diced shallot </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
