        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ground cumin </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>(save the rest for later!) and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> sweetcorn </strong>(no need to drain),<strong> </strong>50ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[85ml]</span> <strong>water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for an initial 5 min</p><p>After an initial 5 min remove the lid and cook, uncovered, for a further 3-4 min or until most of the liquid has absorbed, then remove from the heat – this is your<strong> spiced corn</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
